sentences.en: When the chaos of feelings receded, and i slowly became aware of myself again, Mameha was kneeling above me.

sentences.en: I sank down right where I was, kneeling there at the edge of the clearing, beginning to gasp.
sentences.vi: Tôi quỳ xuống ngay chỗ đang đứng, quỳ ở chỗ bìa rừng trống đó, bắt đầu thở hổn hển.

sentences.en: The girl kneeling on the other side was no older than Satsu, but thin and nervous as a bird.
sentences.vi: Cô gái quỳ ở phía bên kia cửa không lớn hơn satsu, nhưng gầy gò và nhát gan như con chim.

sentences.en: I'm sure the doctor felt grand to have two such ornately dressed women kneeling at his feet that way.

sentences.en: Nobu and i did our best to keep the Minister kneeling in the doorway with his head suspended over the snow.

sentences.en: When i returned to the okiya, Pumpkin was kneeling on the walkway near the courtyard, making terrible twanging noises with her Shamisen.

sentences.en: At one point i think i convinced myself i wasn't even in the exhibition hall but in a quiet room kneeling beside the Chairman.
sentences.vi: Đôi lúc tôi có cảm giác như mình không phải đang ngồi trong nhà biểu diễn mà đang ở trong một căn phòng yên tĩnh quỳ một bên ông chủ tịch.

sentences.en: Of course, a geisha never really sits while wearing kimono; what we call sitting is probably what other people would call kneeling.
sentences.vi: Dĩ nhiên, người geisha không ngồi trong khi mặc kimono; cái thế mà chúng tôi gọi là ngồi có lẽ những người khác gọi là quỳ.
